                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1120.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 25, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Vilbrun Guillaume Sam entered Port au Prince this morning at 9, escorted by about
                    300 mounted troops. His army of about 3000 had preceded him into the city.
                    Presidential salutes fired from forts. Perfect order maintained.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
